desc: A coffee beer I can get much more behind. The coffee is there but the stout flavours come through stronger and balance it out. Very rich and creamy

name: The mill solitary bliss
desc: Good heavy west coast IIPA. Pretty easy drinking despite the strength

name: Blackmans needs more cascade
desc: A heavy dose of hops strong on the citrus. Has a nice little tang at the end that makes you want to come back for another sip.A good old school IPA

name: Tallboy and moose highly illogical DIPA
desc: Kind of strange mix of hops, there’s a juicy flavour coming through with a bit of an orange taste but also some more earthy hops. It gets better the more you drink as the juicy flavours become more prominent

name: Frenchies soft tropical mist
desc: Has a good level of flavour for a mid strength but light enough that you could still easily keep knocking these back. Zesty on the nose with a little citrus tang on the tongue

name: Thunder road mandarin oat cream IPA
desc: This is the second mandarin and cream beer I’ve had. It sounds awful but somehow keeps working perfectly, the 2 flavours complement each other and the rest of the beer

name: Sierra Nevada hoppy anniversary ale
desc: Heavy hoppy ale, kind of a level between regular and the torpedo. Food somehow enhances the hops

name: Zytho white stout
desc: Malty to the point where it actually tastes like a vanilla malt shake. Love this interesting take on a stout. Wish I had a glass for this

name: White rabbit sour red
desc: Red and sour seem to go well together

name: Brouhaha hinterland XPA
desc: Fairly standard XPA, a little more restrained than the Balter. It’s good, but not exciting

name: Panhead pep torque
desc: Probably the first time I’ve liked watermelon in a beer

name: Deeds primal horde
desc: Creamy and citrusy, a great combination

name: Lab ouroboros
desc: I was hoping for a bitter red ale but this is a Flemish red ale so actually more of a sour. Not a style I see very often, very refreshing

name: All inn what’s up my grinches
desc: Very light on the vanilla but otherwise a good stout. There is a bit of sweetness which probably goes against the name. One of those beers that gets better thee more you drink

name: Alesmith IPA
desc: Strong IPA with lots of rich flavours. Proper west coast IPA with nothing floral or citrusy. Enough alcohol to warm the body

name: Ballistic IPA
desc: Middle of the road IPA

name: Prancing pony the piper
desc: Slightly tropical west coast IPA. Pretty easy drinking

name: Collective arts life in the clouds
desc: Very smooth hazy IPA. Not sure if this beer has been through the wars hence the particulate haze, but still tastes good

name: Reckless pale ale
desc: Very solid pale ale, the kind of beer you would just keep drinking

name: Ballistic mele kalikimaka
desc: Super smooth and pineapplly. Great hazy IPA

name: Frenchies summer XPA
desc: Frenchies really does a good job of making light hazy beers

name: Thunder road exotica 4
desc: There’s something off about this.  Maybe I just had too many beers by this point

name: Hop nation humbug
desc: Strong stout flavours and a fair amount of bitterness but somehow smells sweet. It all manages to fit together

name: Two birds total eclipse of the hop
desc: Quite hoppy to start but then manages to mild out. Pretty on point for an XPA. It’s a good XPA, but there’s better ones around

name: Revel mountain IPA
desc: Tastes a lot lighter than most IPA. Very smashable

name: Bridge roads fat man red suit fat sack
desc: Super heavy in both hops and malt. Very rich and Christmasy, but I wouldn’t more than a middy

name: Killer sprocket American stout
desc: Fairly standard stout

name: Wayward I’ll be bock
desc: It’s a strange mix, dark but not a stout and malty but not to the point of a red and then quite bitter but not as much as an IPA

name: Nomad Rudolphs little helper
desc: It’s trying to be both full of tropical hops and amber malts at the same time, they tend to fight each other a bit to come to the front. Each flavour tends to come to the front on alternate sips . But overall it is a pretty good amber ale, and nice to see something different

name: Hawthorn unicorn
desc: Solid middle of the road NEIPA. I just got it for the silly picture but it turned out really good, was the best beer I found that night

name: Willie the boatman no way Jose
desc: A little harsh on the stomach

name: Bridge road magical Christmas unicorn
desc: Super creamy but with a mild taste

name: Yulli’s Eugene
desc: Decent lager, a nice break after a week of heavy beers

name: Revel American brown ale
desc: Nice sweet, slightly nutty brown ale

name: Black hops eggnog stout
desc: It’s like a spiced stout. A tad of ginger and something else from Christmas

name: Grifter voodoo paradise
desc: Super creamy nitro stout

name: Boatrocker life
desc: All sorts of strange. Usually barley wines are very sweet but this has a tang to it. Perhaps it was a little cold when I started drinking, as it warmed the sweetness came through more but without getting sickly. One of the nicer barley wines I’ve had

name: 10 toes black
desc: Has a lot of tropical flavours for a mid strength

name: Akasha talus
desc: Similar to other IPAs from Akasha but with a little something extra that I can’t pick. Whatever it is, it’s delicious

name: 10 toes clockwork apricot
desc: Super mild double IPA, to the point where you wouldn’t hesitate to have quite a few. Takes a while to get the apricot to come through which I think is what mellows it out

name: White bay dreaming
desc: Fairly classical Belgian wit beer. A little yeasty, but not really that exciting. Lots of better options around

name: 10 toes pipeline pale ale
desc: Very light refreshing pale ale. Just a hint of tropical hops

name: Red right hand red IPA
desc: Rich caramel flavours but not much in the way of hops but has a little bitterness

name: Slipstream big billy
desc: It’s a pale ale with a little extra kick. The tropical hops come off with a little tangerine tang. All fits together really well

name: One drop toasted coconut pineapple nitro milkshake IPA
desc: The nitro pour instructions didn’t work too well but it is very smooth. Smells like a Pina colada with lots of coconut coming through and then the pineapple comes through more in the taste. Surprisingly easy to drink given all the things going on in this beer, sadly it’s a once off beer because I could go for some more of these. I really like the way one drop do milkshake IPAs

name: Bloke lager
desc: I like the can design but the beer itself is very boring. Just your regular dry lager

name: Blasta unbridled unicorn
desc: Classical west coast IIPA which gives a nice kick in the face. Leaves a lot of fruity hops on the tip of the tongue along with a hit of bitterness

name: One drop three cubed
desc: Great west coast IPA without any fruity or tropical hops but lots of caramel and bitterness. It’s very smooth for the amount of flavour. I do love a good old school IPA

name: Little bang face inverter
desc: Some people like a little bit of lemon in their beer, this is like someone put a little bit of beer in a glass of lemon. As a beer lover, it’s not really to my taste

name: Urbanaut beer blender coconut. Hazy + pineapple sour
desc: Interesting concept, it’s sold as 2 cans joined together designed to be mixed together. The hazy IPA was nice but the sour was a bit too much. Together they mellow each other out, the super sour smell is still there but not as much in the taste. It comes out a little more orangey than I would expect. It’s a fun novelty, but not enough to make me choose it over a standard beer

name: Holgate twin suns XPA
desc: Different from most XPAs out there, a little bit punchier and a more piney choice of hops

name: Devils hollow flash Kate
desc: It’s an ok IPA but doesn’t really have a lot of hops coming through

name: Stubbie
desc: Fairly harsh bitterness without much flavour. Mostly having this as a break between stronger beers

name: White bay union
desc: Very crisp lager, nice to see something not going either malty or dry

name: Philter IIPA
desc: Slightly dank but well rounded. Very nice IPA

name: Kereru resonator
desc: Quite a harsh bitterness, ok but no more

name: Tallboy and moose 2 solid 2 gold
desc: Seems like it has gone past the best before. Harsh bitterness without much else

name: Frenchies tropical brut IPA
desc: Very tropical and refreshing. A little bit of pineapple but not enough to be harsh. Full of flavour but easy to drink

name: Black hops G.O.A.T
desc: Mild hazy IPA. Hard to really pick any specific flavours. One of those tasty yet kind of boring beers

name: Grassy knoll valley lager
desc: Quite a light lager with a very mild fruity tang. A good start to the drinking day and a nice beer for by the pool

name: Ballistic water me lawn
desc: Hits the mark for a gose of being salty and mildly sour. Very little head and a slightly hazy yellow colour. Watermelon comes through very mild in both smell and taste

name: Blackflag tropical pale ale
desc: Nice tropical pale ale, but nothing that exciting

name: Ocean reach tropical XPA
desc: Nice clear XPA with a good head. A bit more bland than the label suggests, just doesn’t have much in the way of tropical flavours

name: Monteith’s Phoenix IPA
desc: Pleasantly surprised with this, no big flavours but a solid strong bitterness that you would expect from an IPA

name: Garage project white chocolate beer
desc: The nitro makes this really creamy and the white chocolate comes through. After that the raspberry is there but still enough like a beer to keep me happy

name: Old wives ale I can has IBU
desc: Pretty high on the IBU as advertised, not much else going on. It's very rich

name: Brick lane Revolver
desc: Not getting much hoppiness, but a lot of maltyness from the dark grain. Takes a while to get acclimated to and even then it’s not exciting me

name: Bridge road fruit salad sour
desc: Does taste quite a lot like a fruit salad. Lots of pineapple but it’s a little artificial. Delivers on what it says

name: Hope lager
desc: Like a really dry Australian lager but with a little metallic zing. I think this might have been in the can too long because the taste and the smell just don’t seem right. Once the head died the bad flavours went away a little, but there wasn’t much left then

name: Hop nation coffee pastry stout
desc: Smells of coffee but tastes more of chocolate and pastry

name: Obrien pale ale
desc: There’s nothing crazy about this beer, but it’s quite refined and very easy drinking

name: Hughie
desc: Slightly malty lager

name: Chur road Conan
desc: Does have a good bit of orange coming through. Pretty nice IPA that isn’t too heavy to have more of

name: Hawkers knafeh habibi
desc: A very cake like stout. I do like how they have mixed pastry and beer. Hard to pick individual flavours but I do like it

name: Deep creek hoppy McHop face
desc: Not as heavy on the hops as I would expect, more of a smooth west coast IPA. As it warms the hop oils come through more strongly but it still seems milder than you would expect. If you’re new to DIPAs then this is for you

name: Young Henry’s passionfruit and guava sour
desc: Smells a little strange, mild sourness. Lives somewhere between a beer and a cider

name: Frenchies pilsner
desc: Decent pilsner, not too malty. Matches well with dumplings

name: Stomping ground Gipps St
desc: Quite a lot of dank hops on the nose for a pale ale but that’s not a complaint in any way.  Still easy drinking enough and very enjoyable

name: West city NEIPA
desc: Has a juicy taste but it’s undercut by a harshness that kind of ruins it. By the end I’m ok with it, but it’s not one to look for

name: Bira 91 blonde
desc: Malty lager, probably too heavy on the malt

name: Sauce double infrared
desc: That little bit of rye makes this an amazing red ale. Rich, bitter and beautiful

name: Bondi draught
desc: Fairly light lager. Easy drinking

name: Garage project trip hop
desc: With the lower alcohol percentage the rich flavours you would expect from a triple hop don’t come through, but perhaps that’s the point. The flavours don’t build up and slow down the drinking. Not my style because I’m ok with heavier beers but has nice flavours

name: Revision IPA
desc: Very nicely rounded, good depth of hops that leaves a little tingle on the tongue. Can’t really fault this, nothing crazy going on, just a tasty, easy drinking IPA

name: John Boston the end island IPA
desc: Very mild for an IPA but actually pretty nice. Easy drinking with very little heavy hops

name: Big shed erebus
desc: Lots of coffee in the smell but less in the taste. Very thick and heavy with a little bit of tang that somehow just dissolves leaving nothing but happiness

name: Sydney hylander session IPA
desc: Light beer but with a little extra bit of hops. Pretty high in ABV for a session ale which I personally like

name: Rodenbach Alexander
desc: Tastes a lot of sour cherries but mixed in with beer. Very different but I like it

name: Sydney Potts point porter
desc: Pretty on point porter. It’s much thinner than the stouts out there. There’s a little bit of coffee but it’s very mild. A good refreshing dark beer

name: Cattle yard summer red
desc: Kind of sweet red ale. Very light as well which makes it easy to drink. Good choice if starting out with red ales

name: Black hops Neverland
desc: Absolutely amazing. I don’t know how grapefruit comes out creamy instead of bitter. The percentage is so small on the can I didn’t even know it was this strong until I was half way through. Smells a little fruity and sweet but tastes much more mellow. Made me sad when the glass ran out

name: Bad shepherd break yo fast
desc: Smells a bit like maple but the general beer smell covers it a bit but fades . It initially tastes very smokey but that subsides and a lot of the sweetness comes through

name: Thunder road Margarita Gose
desc: It does have that lime and tequila taste that you get with a margarita in the taste but it smells more like a beer. It’s the kind of sour I like where it uses the sourness to pull flavours from other things into a normal light beer. It’s very easy to drink but it’s not the kind of beer that makes me want more

name: Bentspoke sprocket
desc: Middle of the road IPA. Good for both a bit of flavour and for having a few of them

name: Mountain culture scenic route
desc: Very hazy for a session IPA. Smells very tropical. It’s got some juicy flavours but also a little harshness in the finish which does diminish towards the end of the glass

name: Mountain culture lager
desc: Not that much to say about lagers. It’s clean and crisp

name: 3 ravens shake
desc: It’s all sorts of salted caramel mixed with beer

name: Mountain culture moon dust stout
desc: Nice thick stout. Pretty much the perfect example of what a standard stout should be

name: Sierra Nevada calafornia IPA
desc: Very light for an IPA but nice and tropical. Does not do well after it warms up, comes across like a bad lager

name: Mountain culture laser quest
desc: Looks sweet, but it’s just sour, but really only mildly. Goes down almost like water after a while. Great neutral beer to cleanse the palette

name: Black hops east coast low
desc: Easy drinking tropical pale ale. Light, refreshing and tasty

name: Mountain culture cult juice
desc: Great hazy beer. Super tropical and juicy, full of flavour. Absolutely delicious

name: Range informal disco
desc: Nice juicy hazy IPA, a little bit of pineapple and peach. By itself it’s very smooth but with food it’s a little too bitter. Overall very nice

name: Willie the boatman tempe tim
desc: Very mild pale but very good for an easy drinking mid strength

name: Tallboy and moose deadset lager
desc: Pretty good lager with a bit of sweetness and a fresh finish

name: Garage project fuck yeah 2021
desc: Very juicy without any harshness at all. Great from the first sip to the last

name: bracket only one night
desc: I could drink this all day despite how strong it is

name: Mountain goat botanical IPA
desc: It’s like a gin and tonic but in beer form

name: For the road park draught
desc: Little bit of sweetness but not any maltiness. A little bit harsh towards the end. But overall very easy drinking without much flavour

name: White rabbit golden sour
desc: Very mild sour. Easy drinking

name: Two birds chew tang clan
desc: Golden orange colour with a slightly yeasty aroma and a hint of cloves. Has the little tang in the taste that the name promises
